JAKARTA, May 24 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President B.J.
Habibie Monday instructed Attorney General Andi M. Ghalib to study intensively all the data provided by the U.S. Time magazine on the alleged wealth of former President Soeharto and his family abroad.
"But (the investigation on former President Soeharto's allegedly hidden wealth) should abide by the concept of (respect for) human rights," State Secretary/Justice Minister Muladi quoted Habibie as saying after a meeting with Ghalib, Defense Minister Gen. Wiranto and himself at the Merdeka Palace here.
